  "text": "Under single-resource limitation, the quotas of the limiting metals were greatly reduced ( Mn at concentrations that limit the growth T. pseudonana were not inhibited by the presence of Fe in the medium ( SOD activity-To examine the biochemical basis for the increased Mn requirement of low-Fe cells, we chose to focus on the coastal species: T. pseudonana because it was easy to colimit and T. weissflogii because its Q Mn was reported to increase under Fe deficiency [CITATION_1] . Iron deficiency increased SOD activity in both species by 1.4 and 1.6 times, respectively (Table 4 ; t-test; P Ͻ 0.05). In T. weissflogii, the increased SOD activity coincided with an increase in the generation of ROS, which suggests that the cells experienced greater oxidative stress under low-than high-Fe conditions.",
